"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:3.12\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">3.12</span> Storehouse</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">בַּיִת, אָסֹף</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">((beyth) ’asupim)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:25\">NEH 12:25</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">אוֹצָר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(’otsar)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:27\">1CH 27:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:28\">1CH 27:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:11\">2CH 11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:44\">NEH 12:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:12\">NEH 13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:13\">NEH 13:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:22\">JOB 38:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:22\">JOB 38:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:7\">PSA 33:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:7\">PSA 135:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa39:2\">ISA 39:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa39:4\">ISA 39:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:13\">JER 10:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:11\">JER 38:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:16\">JER 51:16</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ἀποδοχεῖον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(apodocheion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir1:17\">SIR 1:17</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">θησαυρός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(thēsauros)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir41:12\">SIR 41:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir43:14\">SIR 43:14</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ταμεῖον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(tameion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:24\">LUK 12:24</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The places listed above were for general storage. Their shape and structure are undefined. See also <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">3.13.4 Armory, arsenal&lt;REALIA:3.13.4&gt;</a> and <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">3.14.1.4 Treasury, strongroom&lt;REALIA:3.14.1.4&gt;</a>.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>In most of the references listed above it is stated what was being stored. Where the commodity being stored is named, languages may have a special word for the particular place where such a commodity is stored; for example, in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:27\">1CH 27:27</a><abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> has “Wine cellars” for the Hebrew word <em>’otsar</em>. However, in the following verse, where the same word is used together with “oil,” <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> has “Olive oil storage,” because English has no special word for a place to store olive oil.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
